ity. This clear-eyed and thorough biography explores how Bialik overcame intense personal struggles to become a charismatic literary leader at the core of modern Hebrew culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAuthors, HebrewvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300227741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300227741.jpg  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles